#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:21
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now that your kernel is configured and compiled and the necessary system\n"
"configuration files are filled in correctly, it is time to install a\n"
"program that will fire up your kernel when you start the system. Such a\n"
"program is called a <e>bootloader</e>. For x86, Gentoo Linux provides <uri\n"
"link=\"#grub\">GRUB</uri> and <uri link=\"#lilo\">LILO</uri>. But before we\n"
"install one of these two bootloaders, we inform you how to configure framebuffer\n"
"(assuming you want it of course). With framebuffer you can run the Linux command\n"
"line with (limited) graphical features (such as using the nice bootsplash\n"
"image Gentoo provides).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: Framebuffer"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:39
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<e>If</e> you have configured your kernel with framebuffer support (or you used\n"
"<c>genkernel</c>'s default kernel configuration), you can activate it by adding\n"
"a <c>vga</c> and/or a <c>video</c> statement to your bootloader configuration \n"
"file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:46
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First of all you need to know what type of framebuffer device you're using. If\n"
"you use a Gentoo patched kernel tree (such as <c>gentoo-sources</c>) you will\n"
"have had the possibility of selecting <c>vesafb-tng</c> as the <e>VESA driver\n"
"type</e> (which is default for these kernel sources). If this is the case, you\n"
"are using <c>vesafb-tng</c> and do not need to set a <c>vga</c> statement.\n"
"Otherwise you are using the <c>vesafb</c> driver and need to set the <c>vga</c>\n"
"statement.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:56
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <c>vga</c> statement controls the resolution and color depth of your\n"
"framebuffer screen for <c>vesafb</c>. As stated in\n"
"<path>/usr/src/linux/Documentation/fb/vesafb.txt</path> (which gets installed\n"
"when you install a kernel source package), you need to pass the VESA number \n"
"corresponding to the requested resolution and color depth to it.\n"
msgstr ""

