#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:201
#, no-wrap
msgid "To install GRUB, let's first emerge it:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:205
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge grub</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:209
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Although GRUB is now installed, we still need to write up a\n"
"configuration file for it and place GRUB in our MBR so that GRUB automatically \n"
"boots your newly created kernel. Create <path>/boot/grub/grub.conf</path> with\n"
"<c>nano</c> (or, if applicable, another editor):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:215
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating /boot/grub/grub.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:216
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>nano -w /boot/grub/grub.conf</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:220
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now we are going to write up a <path>grub.conf</path>. Below you'll\n"
"find two possible <path>grub.conf</path> for the partitioning example we use \n"
"in this guide. We've \n"
"only extensively commented the first <path>grub.conf</path>. Make sure you use\n"
"<e>your</e> kernel image filename and, if appropriate, <e>your</e> initrd image\n"
"filename.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:230
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The first <path>grub.conf</path> is for people who have not used \n"
"    <c>genkernel</c> to build their kernel\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:234
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The second <path>grub.conf</path> is for people who have used\n"
"    <c>genkernel</c> to build their kernel\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><note>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:240
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If your root filesystem is JFS, you <e>must</e> add \" ro\" to the <c>kernel</c>\n"
"line since JFS needs to replay its log before it allows read-write mounting.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:244
#, no-wrap
msgid "grub.conf for non-genkernel users"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:245
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment># Which listing to boot as default. 0 is the first, 1 the second etc.</comment>\n"
"default 0\n"
"<comment># How many seconds to wait before the default listing is booted.</comment>\n"
"timeout 30\n"
"<comment># Nice, fat splash-image to spice things up :)\n"
"# Comment out if you don't have a graphics card installed</comment>\n"
"splashimage=(hd0,0)/boot/grub/splash.xpm.gz\n"
"\n"
"title=Gentoo Linux 2.6.12-r10\n"
"<comment># Partition where the kernel image (or operating system) is located</comment>\n"
"root (hd0,0)\n"
"kernel /boot/kernel-2.6.12-gentoo-r10 root=/dev/hda3\n"
"\n"
"<comment># The next four lines are only if you dualboot with a Windows system.</comment>\n"
"<comment># In this case, Windows is hosted on /dev/hda6.</comment>\n"
"title=Windows XP\n"
"rootnoverify (hd0,5)\n"
"makeactive\n"
"chainloader +1\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:266
#, no-wrap
msgid "grub.conf for genkernel users"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:267
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"default 0\n"
"timeout 30\n"
"splashimage=(hd0,0)/boot/grub/splash.xpm.gz\n"
"\n"
"title=Gentoo Linux 2.6.12-r10\n"
"root (hd0,0)\n"
"kernel /boot/kernel-genkernel-x86-2.6.12-gentoo-r10 root=/dev/ram0 init=/linuxrc ramdisk=8192 real_root=/dev/hda3 udev\n"
"initrd /boot/initramfs-genkernel-x86-2.6.12-gentoo-r10\n"
"\n"
"<comment># Only in case you want to dual-boot</comment>\n"
"title=Windows XP\n"
"rootnoverify (hd0,5)\n"
"makeactive\n"
"chainloader +1\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:284
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you used a different partitioning scheme and/or kernel image, adjust\n"
"accordingly. However, make sure that anything that follows a GRUB-device (such\n"
"as <path>(hd0,0)</path>) is relative to the mountpoint, not the root. In other\n"
"words, <path>(hd0,0)/grub/splash.xpm.gz</path> is in reality\n"
"<path>/boot/grub/splash.xpm.gz</path> since <path>(hd0,0)</path> is\n"
"<path>/boot</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:293
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Besides, if you chose to use a different partitioning scheme and did not put\n"
"<path>/boot</path> in a separate partition, the <path>/boot</path> prefix used\n"
"in the above code samples is really <e>required</e>. If you followed our\n"
"suggested partitioning plan, the <path>/boot</path> prefix it not required, but\n"
"a <path>boot</path> symlink makes it work. In short, the above examples should\n"
"work whether you defined a separate <path>/boot</path> partition or not.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:302
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you need to pass any additional options to the kernel, simply add\n"
"them to the end of the kernel command. We're already passing one option\n"
"(<c>root=/dev/hda3</c> or <c>real_root=/dev/hda3</c>), but you can pass others \n"
"as well, such as the <c>video</c> and/or <c>vga</c> statements for framebuffer \n"
"as we discussed previously.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:310
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:566
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you're using a 2.6.7 or higher kernel and you jumpered your harddrive\n"
"because the BIOS can't handle large harddrives you'll need to append\n"
"<c>hdx=stroke</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:316
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:572
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<c>genkernel</c> users should know that their kernels use the same boot options\n"
"as is used for the Installation CD. For instance, if you have SCSI devices, you\n"
"should add <c>doscsi</c> as kernel option.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:322
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now save the <path>grub.conf</path> file and exit. You still need to install \n"
"GRUB in the MBR (Master Boot Record) so that GRUB is automatically executed when\n"
"you boot your system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:328
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The GRUB developers recommend the use of <c>grub-install</c>. However, if for\n"
"some reason <c>grub-install</c> fails to work correctly you still have the\n"
"option to manually install GRUB.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:334
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Continue with <uri link=\"#grub-install-auto\">Default: Setting up GRUB using\n"
"grub-install</uri> or <uri link=\"#grub-install-manual\">Alternative: Setting up\n"
"GRUB using manual instructions</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:342
#, no-wrap
msgid "Default: Setting up GRUB using grub-install"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:346
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To install GRUB you will need to issue the <c>grub-install</c> command.\n"
"However, <c>grub-install</c> won't work off-the-shelf since we are inside a\n"
"chrooted environment. We need to create <path>/etc/mtab</path> which lists all\n"
"mounted filesystems. Fortunately, there is an easy way to accomplish this -\n"
"just copy over <path>/proc/mounts</path> to <path>/etc/mtab</path>, excluding\n"
"the <c>rootfs</c> line if you haven't created a separate boot partition. The\n"
"following command will work in both cases:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:355
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating /etc/mtab"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:356
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>grep -v rootfs /proc/mounts &gt; /etc/mtab</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:360
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now we can install GRUB using <c>grub-install</c>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:363
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running grub-install"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:364
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>grub-install /dev/hda</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:368
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:436
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you have more questions regarding GRUB, please consult the <uri\n"
"link=\"http://www.gnu.org/software/grub/grub-faq.html\">GRUB FAQ</uri> or the <uri\n"
"link=\"http://www.gnu.org/software/grub/manual/\">GRUB Manual</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:374
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:448
#, no-wrap
msgid "Continue with <uri link=\"#reboot\">Rebooting the System</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:380
#, no-wrap
msgid "Alternative: Setting up GRUB using manual instructions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:384
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To start configuring GRUB, you type in <c>grub</c>. You'll be presented\n"
"with the <path>grub&gt;</path> grub command-line prompt. Now, you need to type \n"
"in the right commands to install the GRUB boot record onto your hard drive.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:389
#, no-wrap
msgid " Starting the GRUB shell"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:390
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>grub</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><note>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:394
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If your system does not have any floppy drives, add the <c>--no-floppy</c>\n"
"option to the above command to prevent grub from probing the (non-existing) \n"
"floppy drives.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:400
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In the example configuration we want to install GRUB so that it reads its \n"
"information from the boot-partition <path>/dev/hda1</path>, and installs the \n"
"GRUB boot record on the hard drive's MBR (master boot record) so that the first\n"
"thing we see when we turn on the computer is the GRUB prompt. Of course, if you\n"
"haven't followed the example configuration during the installation,\n"
"change the commands accordingly.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:409
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The tab completion mechanism of GRUB can be used from within GRUB.\n"
"For instance, if you type in \"<c>root (</c>\" followed by a TAB, you will\n"
"be presented with a list of devices (such as <path>hd0</path>). If you\n"
"type in \"<c>root (hd0,</c>\" followed by a TAB, you will receive a list\n"
"of available partitions to choose from (such as <path>hd0,0</path>).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:417
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"By using the tab completion, setting up GRUB should be not that hard.\n"
"Now go on, configure GRUB, shall we? :-)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:421
#, no-wrap
msgid " Installing GRUB in the MBR"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:422
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"grub&gt; <i>root (hd0,0)</i>          <comment>(Specify where your /boot partition resides)</comment>\n"
"grub&gt; <i>setup (hd0)</i>           <comment>(Install GRUB in the MBR)</comment>\n"
"grub&gt; <i>quit</i>                  <comment>(Exit the GRUB shell)</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><note>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:428
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you want to install GRUB in a certain partition instead of the MBR,\n"
"you have to alter the <c>setup</c> command so it points to the right\n"
"partition. For instance, if you want GRUB installed in\n"
"<path>/dev/hda3</path>, then the command becomes <c>setup (hd0,2)</c>.\n"
"Few users however want to do this.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><note>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:442
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When you reinstall a kernel, you do not need to copy over the files anymore.\n"
"Just run <c>make install</c> after compiling the kernel; it will automatically\n"
"copy the necessary files and adjust the GRUB configuration.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:455
#, no-wrap
msgid "Alternative: Using LILO"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:457
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:474
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing LILO"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:461
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"LILO, the LInuxLOader, is the tried and true workhorse of Linux\n"
"bootloaders. However, it lacks some features that GRUB has (which is\n"
"also the reason why GRUB is currently gaining popularity). The reason\n"
"why LILO is still used is that, on some systems, GRUB doesn't work and\n"
"LILO does. Of course, it is also used because some people know LILO and\n"
"want to stick with it. Either way, Gentoo supports both, and apparently\n"
"you have chosen to use LILO.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:471
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing LILO is a breeze; just use <c>emerge</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:475
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge lilo</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:481
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring LILO"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:485
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To configure LILO, you must create <path>/etc/lilo.conf</path>. Fire up\n"
"your favorite editor (in this handbook we use <c>nano</c> for\n"
"consistency) and create the file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:490
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating /etc/lilo.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:491
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>nano -w /etc/lilo.conf</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:495
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Some sections ago we have asked you to remember the kernel-image name\n"
"you have created. In the next example <path>lilo.conf</path> we also use the\n"
"example partitioning scheme. There are two separate parts: \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:502
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    One for those who have not used <c>genkernel</c> to build their kernel\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:505
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    One for those who have used <c>genkernel</c> to build their kernel\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:510
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Make sure you use <e>your</e> kernel image filename and, if appropriate,\n"
"<e>your</e> initrd image filename.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><note>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:515
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If your root filesystem is JFS, you <e>must</e> add an <c>append=\"ro\"</c> line\n"
"to each boot image since JFS needs to replay its log before it allows \n"
"read-write mounting.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:520
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example /etc/lilo.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:521
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"boot=/dev/hda             <comment># Install LILO in the MBR</comment>\n"
"prompt                    <comment># Give the user the chance to select another section</comment>\n"
"timeout=50                <comment># Wait 5 (five) seconds before booting the default section</comment>\n"
"default=gentoo            <comment># When the timeout has passed, boot the \"gentoo\" section</comment>\n"
"\n"
"<comment># For non-genkernel users</comment>\n"
"image=/boot/kernel-2.6.12-gentoo-r10\n"
"  label=gentoo            <comment># Name we give to this section</comment>\n"
"  read-only               <comment># Start with a read-only root. Do not alter!</comment>\n"
"  root=/dev/hda3          <comment># Location of the root filesystem</comment>\n"
"\n"
"<comment># For genkernel users</comment>\n"
"image=/boot/kernel-genkernel-x86-2.6.12-gentoo-r10\n"
"  label=gentoo\n"
"  read-only\n"
"  root=/dev/ram0\n"
"  append=\"init=/linuxrc ramdisk=8192 real_root=/dev/hda3 udev\"\n"
"  initrd=/boot/initramfs-genkernel-x86-2.6.12-gentoo-r10\n"
"\n"
"<comment># The next two lines are only if you dualboot with a Windows system.</comment>\n"
"<comment># In this case, Windows is hosted on /dev/hda6.</comment>\n"
"other=/dev/hda6\n"
"  label=windows\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><note>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:547
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you use a different partitioning scheme and/or kernel image, adjust\n"
"accordingly.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:552
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you need to pass any additional options to the kernel, add an\n"
"<c>append</c> statement to the section. As an example, we add the\n"
"<c>video</c> statement to enable framebuffer:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:557
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using append to add kernel options"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:558
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"image=/boot/kernel-2.6.12-gentoo-r10\n"
"  label=gentoo\n"
"  read-only\n"
"  root=/dev/hda3\n"
"  <i>append=\"video=vesafb:mtrr,ywrap,1024x768-32@85\"</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:579
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now save the file and exit. To finish up, you have to run <c>/sbin/lilo</c> so\n"
"LILO can apply the <path>/etc/lilo.conf</path> to your system (i.e. install\n"
"itself on the disk). Keep in mind that you'll also have to rerun\n"
"<c>/sbin/lilo</c> every time you install a new kernel or make any changes to\n"
"the menu.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:586
#, no-wrap
msgid "Finishing the LILO installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:587
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>/sbin/lilo</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><note>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:591
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When you reinstall a kernel, you do not need to copy over the files anymore.\n"
"Just run <c>make install</c> after compiling the kernel; it will automatically\n"
"copy the necessary files and adjust the LILO configuration.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:597
#, no-wrap
msgid "You can now continue with <uri link=\"#reboot\">Rebooting the System</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:604
#, no-wrap
msgid "Rebooting the System"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:609
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Exit the chrooted environment and unmount all mounted partitions. Then type in \n"
"that one magical command you have been waiting for: <c>reboot</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:613
#, no-wrap
msgid "Unmounting all partitions and rebooting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:614
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>exit</i>\n"
"cdimage ~# <i>cd</i>\n"
"cdimage ~# <i>umount /mnt/gentoo/boot /mnt/gentoo/dev /mnt/gentoo/proc /mnt/gentoo</i>\n"
"cdimage ~# <i>reboot</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:621
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Of course, don't forget to remove the bootable CD, otherwise the CD will be\n"
"booted again instead of your new Gentoo system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2005.1/hb-install-x86-bootloader.xml:626
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once rebooted in your Gentoo installation, finish up with <uri\n"
"link=\"?part=1&amp;chap=11\">Finalizing your Gentoo Installation</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""
